\n<Entry 1>This place is more than a day's walk from any village or town; 
that might be a problem, but it's probably for the best considering 
my past...

\n<Entry 41>The peasants are former serfs from Whiteleaf, recently freed 
from the ruling family. I'm not thrilled about having neighbours, 
but I do admit I missed talking with other people.

Your friend takes in a massive breath as she prepares to 
let loose upon the city, oblivious to the risk to any survivors, 
or even the other Magical Girls! You decide to...

\n<\N[7]>Catch your breath. And stay away from those windows; 
the zombies might be stupid, but they can still see you if you 
make yourself obvious.

\n<\V[1]>You'll just have to put up with a little small talk. Who knows; 
maybe we'll actually get along once we get to know each 
other.

\n<\N[10]>A minor demonic invasion in progress on the underside; 
I'll have to check that, but whatever it is hasn't approached 
the camp...
